  ('gsoc-fossi-openroad-python', 'FOSSi Foundation — Python Bindings for OpenROAD', 'Generate first-class Python bindings for the OpenROAD physical-design tool using SWIG or pybind11 so digital design researchers can script floorplanning, placement and routing from Jupyter notebooks instead of Tcl.', 'Clone github.com/The-OpenROAD-Project/OpenROAD and build with `./etc/Build.sh -no-warnings`. The Tcl boundary is wired through swig in src/main/MakeTcl.cmake — your work either extends that with a Python interpreter or replaces it with pybind11 wrappers.

