  ('gsoc-julia-trixi-fluid-dynamics', 'JuliaLang — GPU Acceleration for Trixi.jl Computational Fluid Dynamics', 'Port selected Trixi.jl discontinuous-Galerkin kernels to CUDA.jl and KernelAbstractions.jl so adaptive-mesh-refined CFD simulations run on a single workstation GPU instead of an MPI cluster. Target apps include compressible Navier-Stokes and MHD.', 'Read github.com/trixi-framework/Trixi.jl — the entry points are src/solvers/dg.jl and src/equations/*. Run examples/structured_2d_dgsem first to learn the framework idioms before optimising.

