Deliverable: load the standard ACES config, set it as a view transform, and round-trip a 32-bit OpenEXR through GIMP retaining the same pixel values an OCIO Nuke node would produce.', 'OpenSource', 'advanced', 'GIMP', 'GSoC', 'GSoC 2023', 'https://developer.gimp.org/core/internship/ideas/', '[{"label":"github.com","url":"https://github.com/colour-science/colour-datasets"}]'::jsonb, '[{"label":"gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gimp","url":"https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gimp","kind":"repo"},{"label":"opencolorio.readthedocs.io/en/latest/","url":"https://opencolorio.readthedocs.io/en/latest/","kind":"docs"}]'::jsonb, ARRAY['c','color','ocio','imaging','gimp']::text[]),
  ('gsoc-gimp-plugin-sandbox', 'GIMP — Sandboxed Plug-in Execution', 'Run GIMP plug-ins inside an OS-level sandbox — seccomp-bpf on Linux, AppContainer on Windows — so importers for risky formats like PSD or RAW cannot read your home directory or open sockets. Touches libgimp and the GIMP plug-in IPC layer.', 'Read app/plug-in and libgimp/gimpplugin.* to understand the existing plug-in protocol. Survey existing sandboxes — Flatpaks bubblewrap is the easiest target on Linux; on macOS and Windows the equivalents differ significantly.

